## What’s mocked vs real

- The LLM Builders are deterministic stand-ins (the calculation logic they “generate” is hard-coded). In production these are real Claude Sonnet calls under the Constitution.
- Z3 verification is reported as PASS/FAIL deterministically. In production this is a real Z3 SMT solver run.
- `fusion_mock.py` mirrors PyFusion’s surface (`Fusion`, `list_catalogs`, `to_df`, semantic layer). In a real POC, replace `import fusion_mock as fusion` with `import fusion`.
- The synthetic fund is the strength, not a limitation. Reproducing edge cases on demand is the asset Fusion does not have.

## What changes for the real POC

1. The auth handshake against `fusion-api.jpmorgan.com`.
1. Fund reconstruction from real Fusion `to_df()` calls instead of the synthetic generator.
1. Real Z3 / dual-Builder runs in place of the deterministic stubs.
1. A side-by-side panel comparing our certified output to the live MSCI swing-pricing module’s output.

Everything else is already wired.